An Act to eliminate the charitable immunity cap.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Section 85K of Chapter 231 of the General Laws, as appearing in the 2022 Official
2 Edition is hereby amended by striking out the entire section and inserting in place thereof the
3 following section:
4 Section 85K. It shall not constitute a defense to any cause of action based on tort brought
5 against a corporation, trustees of a trust, or members of an association that said corporation, trust
6 or association is, or at the time of the cause of action arose was, a charity.
